Overal spread of clarity

: Clearer -> higher the price. / FL: Extremely high mean, but moderate median price.

When we take a look at the boxplot displaying the overall spread of price across all clarity types, corresponding to the claims made on

Threre were some high prices in VS groups, as inclusions are not visible in the naked eye, therefore clarity is not the primary factor affecting the price. However, high-carat diamonds tend to be pricy

clarity_data <-diamonds %>% group_by(clarity) %>% 
  summarize(mean_price = mean(price), median_price = median(price))
